<TITLE> ECNEC approves Tk 5,201 crore in 15 projects </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 29 (bdnews24.com)  The Executive Committee of the National Economic Council Thursday approved 15 development projects involving Tk 5,201 crore. One of the projects was the Tk 1,214 crore Second Emergency Flood Loss Rehabilitation Project for which the ADB will provide Tk 860 crore in funding. In a news briefing, finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam said: "Out of those 15 projects, eight will be implemented with government finances. The remaining seven projects involving Tk 3,025 crore will be financed by the ADB, UNDP and other development organisations." The finance adviser said the objective of the project was to rebuild the necessary infrastructure and revive normal economic and social life of the people affected by recent floods. Work on the project slated to begin on January 1, 2008 will be completed by June 30, 2010. The project was not included in the annual development programme 2007-2008. The project will be implemented by the local government engineering department, the roads and highways department and the Bangladesh Water Development Board, he said. Under the project, the rural infrastructure of 23 districts, the infrastructure of 30 pourashavas and improvements in water resources of 35 districts will be made. Other approved projects include Dhaka water supply development at a cost of Tk 1,466 crore, Tk 89 crore erosion protection project stretching from Panchgaon of Tangibari upazila in Munshiganj and saving Hasail-Banari and Dighirpar unions from Padma erosion. Chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed chaired the ECNEC meeting. bdnews24.com
